.TH CLEAR 1 "2025" "Nightingale" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
clear \- clear the terminal screen
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B clear
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B clear
clears the terminal screen by sending ANSI escape sequences.
.PP
After clearing, the cursor is positioned at the top left of the screen.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B clear
Clear the screen.
.SH NOTES
This command sends ANSI escape codes and will only work on
terminals that support ANSI/VT100 control sequences.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR reset (1),
.BR tput (1)
